records.addlTxt:
Defendant Matthew J Plew in court with attorney Mark P. Powers.  Jayne Davis Dewire appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty of Count #2 of the amended information. Count #1 is dismissed by operation of law.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #2:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT 1 DAY);
3 YEARS OF INTIAL CONFINEMENT;
3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION.

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months. 
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel during the period of probation.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Perform 70 Hours Community Service per each year of community service for a total of 210 Hours. 

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of probation to be forward to Village of Pewaukee Police Department);

DNA SURCHARGE: $200.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of probation).

FINE:  $1569.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  1 YEAR  NON WORKING HOURS w/Standard Release Conditions. Defendant remanded into custody and sentence to begin forthwith. 

Defendant is Eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is Eligible for Sustance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
